==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Imparl
<hw>Im*parl"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>emparler</ets>; pref. <ets>em-</ets> (L. <ets>in</ets>) +
<ets>parler</ets> to speak. See <er>In</er>, prep., and
<er>Parley</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To hold discourse; to
parley.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir. T. North.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>To have time before pleading; to
have delay for mutual adjustment.</def>
<rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imparlance</ent>⟦br⟧
